questiontext.text:
Below are a number of output tables of a series of ANOVA and ANCOVA analyses of cultural participation, measured at time 1 (culpar_1: before the CJP was distributed) and at time 2 (culpar_2) among the same respondents who can be divided into two groups: a group that did not receive a CJP and a group that received a CJP between time 1 and 2 (a group that already had a CJP was not considered).

See analyses 4 and 5. If you take into account the existing differences in cultural participation between the CJP groups at t1, how big are the estimated differences between the ‘no CJP’ group and the ‘new CJP’ group?
